The paper deals with privacy guarantees in networked contexts, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the relationship between differential privacy and inferential privacy, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Laplace noise and influence matrices suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), while the discussion of prior distributions and beliefs suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and social networks (cs.SI).
